"title": "6639: election, to salvation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6639",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God chooses to bring individuals to salvation through faith in Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>Election is part of God's eternal decree</h2>\n<h3>Election is from eternity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:4\">EPH 1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13\">2TH 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim1:9\">2TI 1:9</a></p>\n<h3>Election is God's sovereign prerogative</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:15-Rom9:24\">ROM 9:15–9:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:1-Rom11:6\">ROM 11:1–11:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:19\">EXO 33:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:1\">ISA 65:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:1-Jer18:12\">JER 18:1–18:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:16\">JHN 15:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:6\">JHN 17:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:10-Rom9:13\">ROM 9:10–9:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:10\">EPH 2:10</a></p>\n<h3>God's election places individuals within the covenant of grace</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:7-Neh9:8\">NEH 9:7–9:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:7-Gen15:8\">GEN 15:7–15:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:18-Gen15:21\">GEN 15:18–15:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:19\">GEN 18:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:29\">GAL 3:29</a></p>\n<h3>Election is not on the basis of merit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:26-1Cor1:31\">1CO 1:26–1:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:7-Deut7:8\">DEU 7:7–7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:4-Deut9:6\">DEU 9:4–9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:5\">JAS 2:5</a></p>\n<h2>God's election of his people is the foundation of his saving action</h2>\n<h3>Election does not suspend God's use of the means of salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13-2Thess2:14\">2TH 2:13–2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt1:21\">MAT 1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:8-Eph2:10\">EPH 2:8–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:18\">JAS 1:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>Election works in tandem with the call of the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:14\">MAT 22:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:29-Rom8:30\">ROM 8:29–8:30</a></p>\n<h3>Election is evidenced through a positive response to the gospel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:4-1Thess1:5\">1TH 1:4–1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:37-John6:40\">JHN 6:37–6:40</a></p>\n<h2>Election is a motive for praise</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:28-Rom11:36\">ROM 11:28–11:36</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:3-Eph1:14\">EPH 1:3–1:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:2-1Thess1:4\">1TH 1:2–1:4</a></p>\n<h2>Election is a source of practical comfort</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:31-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:31–8:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:27-John10:29\">JHN 10:27–10:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:2\">JHN 17:2</a></p>\n<h2>Election is an incentive for righteous behaviour</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12-Col3:14\">COL 3:12–3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:16-John15:17\">JHN 15:16–15:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:12-Phil2:13\">PHP 2:12–2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:13-2Thess2:15\">2TH 2:13–2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:3-2Pet1:11\">2PE 1:3–1:11</a></p>\n<h2>Election is a stimulus to the preaching of the gospel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:10\">2TI 2:10</a></strong></p>",
